                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/420.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Consul at Hermosillo</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-19T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1912—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department quotes, for your information, following telegram received from
                    Embassy. [See telegram from the Ambassador to the Secretary, April 17, 1912, 12
                    noon.]</p>
                <p>Is this matter now in the hands of the Governor, or must it be referred to the
                    Central Government? If the former, immediately make arrangements for the entry
                    of 100 rifles and 20,000 rounds of ammunition for the Richardson Construction
                    Co. and of a shipment not to exceed 300 rifles and 30,000 rounds of ammunition
                    which the War Department is sending to you for distribution to Americans in the
                    Yaqui region other than those who will be provided for by Richardson
                    Construction Co., and to Americans in the vicinity of Los Mochis in case they
                    can be reached.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
